original: Danielsson, Åke Gösta Leonard, bankdirektör, Värnamo, f. 26/8/06 i Jönköp. av järnv:tj:man O. L. D. o. Augusta Blom. G. m. Ulla Bauer. Barn: Ulf, Gun. — Stud:ex. i Jönköp. 26, hand :gymn. 27. Anst. v. A-B Gbgs Hand :banks Jönköp.-kont. 27, andre kamrer i Jönköp. Stads o. Läns Sparb., kamrer v. Värnamo Sparb. 42, verkst. dir. där sed. 43. Res. t. Frankr. 37, Tyskl. 39, Danm., Norge 38. Medl. av Frimurarorden o. Par Bricole.
translated: Danielsson, Åke Gösta Leonard, bank director, born August 26th, 1906 in Jönköping to a railroad worker named O.L.D. and Augusta Blom. Married to Ulla Bauer and they have two children, Ulf and Gun. He graduated from high school in Jönköping in 1926 and from a commercial school in 1927. He was employed at A-B Gbgs Hand banks Jönköp.-kont. in 1927 as a second clerk and later worked as an accountant at Jönköping Stads o. Läns Sparb. He became an accountant at Värnamo Sparb. in 1942 and managing director in 1943. He traveled to France in 1937, Germany in 1939, Denmark and Norway in 1938. He was a member of the Freemasonry and Par Bricole organization.
